.SH NAME
FragmentDirective \- FragmentDirective
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]FragmentDirective\f[B]\f[R] interface is an object
exposed to allow code to check whether or not a browser supports text
fragments.
.PP
It is accessed via the \f[CR]Document.fragmentDirective\f[R] property.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
None.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
None.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Checking if text fragments are supported
The code below logs whether or not text fragments are supported in your
browser by checking that \f[CR]Document.fragmentDirective\f[R] is
defined.
Note that the object is empty, and at present is mainly intended for
feature detection.
In the future, it might include other information.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]if\f[R] (document.fragmentDirective) {
  log(\[dq]Your browser supports text fragments.\[dq]);
} \f[B]else\f[R] {
  log(\[dq]Text fragments are not supported in your browser.\[dq]);
}
